        "robots": "index, follow",
        "title": "Hello, Paperboy",
        "twitter": {
          "card": "summary",
        },
      },
      "slug": "hello-paperboy",
      "type": "BlogPost",
      "urlPath": "/blog/hello-paperboy",
    },
    {
      "cv": "<cv>",
      "data": {
        "author": "Paperboy Team",
        "body": "## Listing is a semantic

A blog index is not a *standard page that happens to list things* — it is a **ListPage** with \`listedType: BlogPost\`. The frontend keys off the type, never the URL.",
        "publishDate": "<ts>",
        "summary": "A ListPage lists its child pages of a chosen type — no hardcoded URLs in the frontend.",
        "title": "Modelling listings with ListPage",
      },
      "documentId": "<id-2>",
      "kind": "page",
      "locale": "en",
      "name": "Modelling listings with ListPage",
      "seo": {
        "breadcrumb": [
          {
            "name": "Blog",
            "urlPath": "/blog",
          },
          {
            "name": "Modelling listings with ListPage",
            "urlPath": "/blog/modelling-listings",
          },
        ],
        "canonicalPath": "/blog/modelling-listings",
        "description": "A ListPage lists its child pages of a chosen type — no hardcoded URLs in the frontend.",
        "jsonLd": {
          "@context": "https://schema.org",
          "@type": "BlogPosting",
          "author": {
            "@type": "Person",
            "name": "Paperboy Team",
          },
          "datePublished": "<ts>",
          "description": "A ListPage lists its child pages of a chosen type — no hardcoded URLs in the frontend.",
          "headline": "Modelling listings with ListPage",
          "inLanguage": "en",
        },
        "og": {
          "description": "A ListPage lists its child pages of a chosen type — no hardcoded URLs in the frontend.",
          "image": null,
          "siteName": "Paperboy",
          "title": "Modelling listings with ListPage",
